race.comment: OUR LITTLE STAR (3) is usually thereabouts but finds it hard to win, with only one victory from 19 starts. Has been thereabouts in her first two runs under Nick Olive and should be hitting her straps now. Can't break through this time. PENROSE (10) was quickly into stride and went on to score by 2.5 lengths last time out over 1000m at Queanbeyan. Looks well placed so expect another big run. BURNT TO A CRISP (6) won on debut last time out three-and-a-half weeks ago over 1000m at Wagga, getting home by 0.6 lengths. Everything points to a big run. DENIAL (1) returns and is a noted fresh performer. Readied with a trial and can play a major role.
